        "content": "<p>Hi, I am facing an issue when building a x86 target on <code>rust-next</code> branch: when I run <code>make LLVM=1</code>, I got the following error</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">arch</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">x86</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">include</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">asm</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">processor</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">525</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">17</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">error</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">taking</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">address</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">packed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">member</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">sp0</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">class</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">structure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">x86_hw_tss</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">may</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">an</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unaligned</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pointer</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Werror</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Waddress</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">packed</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">member</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mi\">525</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"n\">this_cpu_write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">cpu_tss_rw</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">x86_tss</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sp0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sp0</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Can anyone confirm that if they encounter the same issue? Or is it a misconfiguration on my end? Thanks!</p>",
